The heavy rains that have pounded the country for the last few weeks have claimed the lives of at least 6 people across the country in the last 24 hours. Three people died in Kajiado county, two in Kilifi while a child drowned in Mihango area of Nairobi at a construction site . This as residients living in Suswa area of Narok county began relocating after the fault lines in the area continued to open up cutting across their homes raising fears that the earth movements would lead to death and destruction. 